  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nWords `Pair` and `Sync` actually have different meanings in terms of our app. And there's currently a mess:\r\n* `Sync` is used instead of `Pair` in most contexts in desktop\r\n* `Pair` is not used in desktop at all\r\n* `Pair` is used in mobile, but not correct everywhere (e.g. after local pairing we say `Devices synced`)\r\n\r\nThese are correct meanings:\r\n* \"Devices Paired\" == \"Devices will be syncing\"\r\n* \"Pair a device\" == \"Setup this device to start syncing with another device\" == \"Setup syncing\"\r\n* \"Unpair a device\" == \"Stop syncing this devices with another device\"\r\n* \"Device Synced\" == \"Device just received some information from another paired device\" (not sure if this should ever be used)\r\n\r\nCompare same screens on Desktop and Mobile:\r\n\r\n| Desktop | Mobile |\r\n|-|-|\r\n| <img width=\"700\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/25482501/65268949-04b9-44e3-9161-bf7b0292a714\"> | <img width=\"600\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/25482501/b63fb9b4-3b92-4431-baef-e4200a417360\"> |\r\n| <img width=\"700\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/25482501/20238d5c-dbf0-4f75-805e-85da3ea51f09\"> | <img width=\"600\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/25482501/a7236ccd-2f56-486f-a198-f4656d2db32e\"> |\r\n\r\n\r\n",
